    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About the Company\n\nWhy We Built Lyric: Supply chains are more critical and complex than ever. Every day, large enterprises navigate trillions of possible decisions that could impact the bottom line. Powerful algorithms and AI can address these problems, yet most organizations struggle to leverage supply chain AI at scale. The current SCM technologies are either rigid, limited-scope point solutions or custom solutions built in-house, which demand immense expertise and investment.\n\nThat is…until now.\n\nEnter Lyric: Lyric is an enterprise AI platform built specifically for supply chains, offering the best of both worlds:\n\n - Out-of-the-box AI solutions for optimizing networks, allocating inventory, scheduling routes, planning fulfillment capacity, promising orders, propagating demand, building predictions, analyzing scenarios, and more, plus\n\n - A platform-first approach that empowers both business and technical users with end-to-end product composability, leveraging no-code tools, their own code, or even forking our code to build and refine supply chain decision intelligence\n\nWith Lyric, enterprises no longer have to choose between flexibility and speed, they get both.\n\nThe Mission: We’re building a new era in supply chain with the team best equipped to lead it. With over 20 years at the intersection of supply chain and algorithms, we developed a deep conviction that global supply chains needed something like Lyric. Since our inception in December 2021, that conviction has been validated time and time again.\n\nToday, a growing number of Fortune 500 companies, including Smurfit WestRock, Estée Lauder, Coca-Cola, and more, are innovating on their own terms with Lyric. We can’t wait to see what our customers, both current and future, are empowered to build with us next. Come build with us!\n\nWe’re looking for a Product Designer to craft intuitive experiences for our AI-first supply chain platform.\n\nYou’ll design for both our Platform Layer (used by data and ML engineers) and our Application Layer (where end-users interact with models and insights).\n\nYour mission: make complex, data-heavy workflows feel simple, coherent, and powerful.\n\n\n🧩 WHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n\nPLATFORM LAYER\n\n - Design intuitive console interfaces for data / ML engineers and modelers\n\n - Create clear workflows for complex data manipulation and model creation\n\n - Develop information architecture for organizing platform tools and assets\n\n\nAPPLICATION LAYER\n\n - Design visual, interactive data visualizations (charts, maps, tables)\n\n - Ensure consistency and clarity across dashboards and output formats\n\n\nGENERAL\n\n - Conduct user research and usability testing to guide design decisions\n\n - Create wireframes, interactive prototypes, and high-fidelity mockups (Figma preferred)\n\n - Collaborate with PMs, engineers, and data scientists throughout development\n\n - Advocate for user-centered design principles and accessibility\n\n - Stay current with the latest trends in UX/UI design, data visualization, and AI interfaces.\n\n\n🧠 WHAT YOU BRING\n\nMust-Haves\n\n - 4-9 years in UX design (B2B or enterprise software preferred)\n\n - Portfolio showcasing complex, data-driven products or workflows\n\n - Fluency in Figma / Sketch / Adobe XD\n\n - Experience with data visualization and information design\n\n - Strong ability to translate technical requirements into human-friendly experiences\n\n - Excellent communication and cross-functional collaboration skills\n\nNice-to-Haves\n\n - Background in supply chain, analytics, or AI tools\n\n - Familiarity with AI/ML concepts and data-driven applications\n\n - Knowledge of HTML / CSS / JavaScript (bonus)\n\n - Understanding of data analysis or statistical concepts\n\n\n✨ WHY JOIN LYRIC\n\n - Design the user experience for the next generation of AI platforms\n\n - Solve meaningful problems that impact global supply chains\n\n - Collaborate with world-class engineers and product leaders\n\n - Work in a culture that values craftsmanship, curiosity, and ownership\n\nIf you’re excited to create beautiful, intuitive experiences for AI-powered systems, we’d love to meet you.\n\n👉 Join us to design the intelligence layer of global supply chains.",
